# React Native Testflight - Project Structure Guide

This repository contains an Expo/React Native module (`react-native-testflight`) with platform-specific native code and an accompanying example application.

## Module entry points

- Public TypeScript API: [src/index.ts](mdc:src/index.ts)
- Shared JavaScript implementation: [src/ReactNativeTestflightModule.ts](mdc:src/ReactNativeTestflightModule.ts)
- iOS native implementation: [ios/ReactNativeTestflightModule.swift](mdc:ios/ReactNativeTestflightModule.swift)
- Android native implementation: [android/src/main/java/expo/modules/testflight/ReactNativeTestflightModule.kt](mdc:android/src/main/java/expo/modules/testflight/ReactNativeTestflightModule.kt)

## Example application

All demo code lives under the [example](mdc:example) directory.

- App entry point: [example/App.tsx](mdc:example/App.tsx)
- Metro entry file: [example/index.ts](mdc:example/index.ts)

## Build configuration & metadata

- Expo module configuration: [expo-module.config.json](mdc:expo-module.config.json)
- Android Gradle root build file: [android/build.gradle](mdc:android/build.gradle)
- iOS CocoaPods specification: [ios/ReactNativeTestflight.podspec](mdc:ios/ReactNativeTestflight.podspec)
